data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"## Deep Investigation Results\n\n**Audit Timestamp:** 2026-02-21T00:24 UTC — I uncovered **5 distinct root causes** creating a cascade of failures across the platform. Here is the complete analysis.\n\n---\n\n### Tool Execution Summary\n\n| # | Tool Requested | Status | Result |\n|---|----------------|:------:|--------|\n| 1 | `admin_system_postgres_raw_query` | ❌ Blocked | Admin MCP `LogRecord` overwrite error — same as health audit |\n| 2 | `loki_search_errors` (agentic-dev, 30m) | ✅ **200 errors** | Massive error storm identified |\n| 3 | `k8s_list_pods` (agentic-dev) | ❌ Blocked | Kubeconfig missing — same persistent issue |\n| 4 | `loki_count_logs` (Milvus failures) | ✅ **7,313 errors** | Quantified ingestion failure rate |\n| 5 | `loki_query` (dimension mismatch) | ✅ Root cause confirmed | Embedding model produces 1024-dim, Milvus expects 1536 |\n| 6 | `loki_query` (Redis errors) | ✅ **3 occurrences** | Redis client API incompatibility found |\n\n---\n\n### Root Cause Analysis\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"Error Cascade - 5 Root Causes\",\n  \"layout\": \"vertical\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"rc1\", \"label\": \"RC1: Embedding Dimension\\nMismatch (1024 vs 1536)\", \"shape\": \"rectangle\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"rc2\", \"label\": \"RC2: Missing Milvus\\nCollections\", \"shape\": \"rectangle\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"rc3\", \"label\": \"RC3: Redis Client API\\nIncompatibility\", \"shape\": \"rectangle\", \"color\": \"warning\"},\n    {\"id\": \"rc4\", \"label\": \"RC4: Schema Mismatch\\n(field 'source' not found)\", \"shape\": \"rectangle\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"rc5\", \"label\": \"RC5: Admin MCP\\nLogRecord Bug\", \"shape\": \"rectangle\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"e1\", \"label\": \"7,313 Milvus\\nwrite failures/30m\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"e2\", \"label\": \"Knowledge Search\\ncompletely broken\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"e3\", \"label\": \"Rate Limiting\\nbypassed\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"warning\"},\n    {\"id\": \"e4\", \"label\": \"RAG Search returns\\n0 results\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"e5\", \"label\": \"Postgres/Redis/Milvus\\nhealth unobservable\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"muted\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"rc1\", \"target\": \"e1\", \"label\": \"every ingestion\"},\n    {\"source\": \"rc2\", \"target\": \"e2\", \"label\": \"collection not found\"},\n    {\"source\": \"rc3\", \"target\": \"e3\", \"label\": \"every chat request\"},\n    {\"source\": \"rc4\", \"target\": \"e4\", \"label\": \"search fails\"},\n    {\"source\": \"rc5\", \"target\": \"e5\", \"label\": \"all admin tools blocked\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### RC1: Embedding Dimension Mismatch (P0 — Highest Volume)\n\n> **7,313 failed writes in 30 minutes** — escalating from ~5/sec to 578/sec\n\n**The smoking gun from Milvus:**\n```\nFailed to execute insert task: the length(1024) of float data should divide the dim(1536)\ncollection=chat_conversations_v2\n```\n\n**The smoking gun from the API:**\n```\nmodel: \"amazon.titan-embed-text-v2:0\"\ndimensions: 1024\n```\n\n| Component | Expected Dimension | Actual Dimension | Status |\n|-----------|:-----------------:|:----------------:|:------:|\n| **Milvus `chat_conversations_v2`** | 1536 | — | Collection schema |\n| **Amazon Titan Embed v2** | — | 1024 | Embedding model |\n| **Result** | — | — | ❌ Every insert rejected |\n\n**Root Cause:** The Milvus collection `chat_conversations_v2` was created with `dim=1536` (likely for OpenAI `text-embedding-ada-002` or `text-embedding-3-large`). The platform was switched to **Amazon Titan Embed v2** which outputs **1024 dimensions**. The `AzureSDKKnowledgeIngester` and `SemanticLearningService` are continuously trying to write 1024-dim vectors into a 1536-dim collection and getting rejected by Milvus.\n\n**Impact:** All new knowledge ingestion is silently failing. The knowledge base is **frozen in time** — no new Azure SDK documentation, no new chat conversation embeddings are being stored.\n\n---\n\n### RC2: Missing Milvus Collections (P0)\n\n```\ncollection not found [database=default] [collection=chat_conversations]\ncollection not found [database=default] [collection=app_documentation]\n```\n\n| Collection | Status |\n|-----------|:------:|\n| `chat_conversations` | ❌ Not found |\n| `app_documentation` | ❌ Not found |\n| `chat_conversations_v2` | ✅ Exists (but dimension mismatch) |\n| `azure_sdk_documentation` | ✅ Exists (but schema mismatch) |\n\n**Root Cause:** Collections `chat_conversations` and `app_documentation` were either never created, dropped during migration, or exist in a different database. The `KnowledgeIngestion` service queries them on every user message and fails silently.\n\n---\n\n### RC3: Redis Client API Incompatibility (P1)\n\n```\nservice: \"ChatAuthService\"\nerror: \"redis.zremrangebyscore is not a function\"\nmsg: \"Rate limit check failed\"\n```\n\n**Occurrences:** 3 in the last 30 minutes (fires on every new chat session).\n\n**Root Cause:** The Redis client library being used by `openagentic-api` does not expose the `zremrangebyscore` method. This is typically caused by:\n- Using `ioredis` v5+ where sorted set commands were renamed\n- Using a Redis cluster client that doesn't support this command directly\n- Redis client was replaced or upgraded without updating calling code\n\n**Impact:** Rate limiting is **completely bypassed**. The `ChatAuthService` catches the error and allows the request through — which means there is **no rate limiting active** on the platform right now.\n\n---\n\n### RC4: Milvus Schema Mismatch — `azure_sdk_documentation` (P1)\n\n```\ncollection=azure_sdk_documentation\nerror=\"field source not exist\"\nOutputFields=\"[content,source,source_url,type,category,priority,metadata]\"\n```\n\n**Root Cause:** The collection `azure_sdk_documentation` (ID: `464399067589254901`) does not have a field called `source`. The application requests it in `OutputFields`, causing every search query against this collection to fail.\n\n---\n\n### RC5: Admin MCP `LogRecord` Bug (P0 — Observability Blocker)\n\n```\nInternal error: \"Attempt to overwrite 'args' in LogRecord\"\n```\n\nThis Python logging framework bug blocks all `admin_system_*` tools, preventing us from running your requested PostgreSQL vacuum query.\n\n---\n\n### Additional Errors Found\n\n| Error | Source | Severity |\n|-------|--------|:--------:|\n| **`Cannot read properties of null (reading 'success')`** | `ChatPipeline` → response attachments | ⚠️ P2 |\n| **Content safety: repetition detected (7x)** | Content filter flagging repeated table rows | ⚠️ P2 |\n| **`ArtifactService` returns 0 results** | Downstream effect of RC2/RC4 — RAG has no data | ❌ P1 |\n\n---\n\n### Recommendations\n\n| Priority | Action | Root Cause | Impact |\n|:--------:|--------|:----------:|--------|\n| **P0** | **Recreate Milvus collections with `dim=1024`** or change embedding model to produce 1536-dim vectors. Run: `collection.alter(dim=1024)` or recreate + backfill. | RC1 | Unblocks **7,313 failed writes/30m** — restores knowledge ingestion |\n| **P0** | **Create missing collections** `chat_conversations` and `app_documentation` with correct 1024-dim schema | RC2 | Restores conversation memory and documentation search |\n| **P0** | **Fix Admin MCP logging** — find the handler that sets `args` on `LogRecord` and rename it (e.g., `log_args`) | RC5 | Unblocks all admin health checks, PostgreSQL queries, Redis/Milvus inspection |\n| **P1** | **Fix Redis rate limiter** — replace `redis.zremrangebyscore()` with `redis.zRemRangeByScore()` (ioredis v5+ camelCase convention) or downpin ioredis | RC3 | Restores rate limiting — currently **completely disabled** |\n| **P1** | **Add `source` field to `azure_sdk_documentation`** collection or remove it from the query's `OutputFields` | RC4 | Restores Azure SDK documentation RAG search |\n| **P2** | **Add null check in ChatPipeline response attachment handler** — `if (result?.success)` instead of `result.success` | Null ref | Prevents silent pipeline errors |\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> **Critical finding:** The combination of RC1 + RC2 + RC4 means **all RAG/knowledge features are effectively non-functional**. The platform is operating as a pure LLM passthrough with no retrieval augmentation. Users are getting responses without any organizational knowledge context. This has been silently degrading quality for every interaction."}

